title: Prep roundup: Glenbard East soccer eliminated, Willowbrook moves on in playoffs
text:
Prep roundup: Glenbard East soccer eliminated, Willowbrook moves on in playoffs Published: Friday, Oct. 23, 2015 11:01 a.m. CDT Caption (Bill Ackerman - backerman@shawmedia.com) Glenbard East's Belgoni Besunda goes for the ball on Aug. 27 in a match against Downers Grove South. The Rams lost against Elk Grove in a regional quarterfinal on Oct. 17 to end their season. By SUBURBAN LIFE MEDIA 
Glenbard East’s boys soccer team saw its season come to an end with a 4-0 loss against Rolling Meadows in a regional quarterfinal game Oct. 17. 
BOYS SOCCER 
Willowbrook 
The Warriors, a No. 10 postseason seed, defeated No. 7 regional host Lake Park 1-0 on Oct. 21 to advance to the regional championship game at 6 p.m. Oct. 24. 
Willowbrook will face No. 1 seed Schaumburg, which defeated Glenbard West in another regional semifinal. 
Montini 
The Broncos’ season ended with an 8-1 loss against St. Francis in a Class 2A regional semifinal Oct. 20. 
GIRLS TENNIS 
Glenbard East 
Kolie Allen advanced to the singles championship match and placed second at the Downers Grove South sectional Oct. 17. 
The sophomore advanced to the state tournament, which began Oct. 22, and the Rams placed fourth as a team at the sectional. 
Willowbrook 
The Warriors placed third at the York sectional Oct. 17 but did not have any players advance to the state tournament. 
Montini 
The Broncos placed ninth at the Downers Grove South sectional Oct. 17. 
GIRLS CROSS COUNTRY 
Glenbard East 
Lexi Weltin (15th, 18:49.1) and Maeve Brasile (16th, 18:49.7) finished neck-and-neck to lead the Rams at the Upstate Eight Conference meet Oct. 17. 
Ali Liljestrand (26th), Cailyn Biegalski (30th), Yoselin Toledo (34th), Jayne Peters (38th) and Olivia Ramos (40th) finished in a cluster for the Rams, who placed fourth as a team. 
Montini 
Emma Makowski (third, 17:55), Gianna Salzbrunn (fourth, 18:05) and Lauren Denemark (11th, 18:24) all had solid races at the Girls Catholic Athletic Conference meet Oct. 17. 
Mary O’Brien and Akayna Collins also were scoring runners as the Broncos tallied 87 points and finished second as a team. 
Willowbrook 
Victoria Palma (14th, 20:07) was the Warriors’ leading runner at the West Suburban Gold meet Oct. 17. 
Willowbrook finished fifth as a team with 120 points. 
BOYS CROSS COUNTRY 
Glenbard East 
Patrick Mikel (34th, 16:30) was East’s top runner at the Upstate Eight Conference meet Oct. 17. The Rams placed 11th as a team. 
Willowbrook 
Marco Martinez placed ninth with a time of 15:52 to lead the way at the West Suburban Gold meet Oct. 17. 
Willowbrook scored 110 points and finished fourth as a team.
